- A real number `c` is *admissible* if for any finite set `A ⊆ ℝ`, if every subset `B ⊆ A` of size `4` satisfies `(B - B).ncard = 11`, then there exists a Sidon subset `S ⊆ A` of size at least `c * |A|` (where `|A|` is the cardinality of `A`). 
